    <p><span><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span></p>
    <p>Regimen: AB <br> Cycle: 28 days, repeat for 2-8 cycles <br>Drug A, 30 mg/m <sup>2</sup>, IV, day 1, 8, 15 and 22 <br>Drug B, 125 mg/ m <sup>2</sup>, IV, day 1 <br> 
 <br>Calculate the total dose per cycle for Drug A and Drug B for a patient measuring 5 feet 8 inches and weighing 160 lb.</p>
    <p><span><strong>Approach: </strong></span>Determine the BSA from nomogram, calculate the quantity of each drug.
<br>Based on the nomogram, BSA of the patient is 1.85 m <sup>2</sup>
</p>
<div class="formulae"><p>$$ Drug  \ A: { 30 { mg \over m^2 } \times 1.85 \ m^2 \times 4 \ days } = 222 \ mg $$</p></div>
<div class="formulae"><p>$$ Drug  \ B: {125 { mg \over m^2 } \times 1.85 \ m^2 \times 1 \ day } = 231.25 mg$$</p></div>
    <p><span><strong>Answer: </strong></span>222 mg, 231.25 mg</p>
